Audit Logging in Hot Path
    format!() + push into growing Vec<String>.
    Heavy allocation + integer formatting cost.
    Hurts both mean and tail latency.
    Fix: structured logging, preallocated ring buffer, or off-core logging.

Unbounded HashMap
    No capacity reservation → repeated reallocation + rehash.
    Non-deterministic latency.
    Pointer chasing hurts cache locality.
    Fix: preallocate, fixed-capacity table, or arena-backed structure.

Poor Cache Locality
    HashMap scatters memory.
    Each lookup touches multiple cache lines.
    Arena-backed contiguous storage is superior.

Dynamic Memory Growth (Vec, HashMap)
    Reallocations cause stop-the-world copies.
    Tail latency spikes.
    Fix: fixed capacity, no growth in steady state.

Large Value Movement via Command Enum
    Order constructed → moved into enum → moved into handler.
    Extra copies and stack pressure.
    Fix: decode directly into storage or use lightweight message structs.


